parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake System Failure (Master Cylinder, Hydraulic System)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the motorcycle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes fail without warning
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the rear brakes lock up
the brakes drag intermittently
a loud scraping noise is audible
the brakes do not work
the motorcycle crashes
and the operator loses control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in recall repair can leave the motorcycle in an unsafe condition, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The parts for the recall repair are unavailable
the manufacturer exceeds a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair
the dealer is unable to determine the cause of the internal brake fluid leak
and the brake system fails to function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The internal brake fluid leak can cause the brake system to fail, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels to the floor
the brake system fails to function properly
and the dealer is unable to determine the cause of the internal brake fluid leak.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the motorcycle to suddenly lose power, leading to a loss of control, which can result in accidents or rear-end collisions.
symptoms: The transmission jumps out of gear
fails to engage
exhibits abnormal grinding noise
downshifts randomly
misses shifts
and causes the motorcycle to lurch forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The insufficient radiator fan clearance can cause the radiator to become damaged, leading to a coolant leak, which can result in a loss of traction and control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Coolant leaking from the radiator
loss of traction at the rear wheel
uncontrolled slide
and crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The front-end wobble or shimmy can cause the motorcycle to become unstable, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The handlebars vibrate or shake violently
the motorcycle pulls to one side
uneven tire wear
abnormal tire noise or "howling"
and a feeling of unsafety on uneven surfaces.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause the motorcycle to become unstable, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The steering stem nut is loose
the lock nut is not properly tightened
the steering bearing adjustment nut is not properly torqued
and a lack of lubricant on the steering bearing adjustment nut threads.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stumbling on cold start can cause the motorcycle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine hesitates or stumbles on cold start
causing the rider to lose control or nearly fall off the motorcycle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tread Splice Failure on Dunlop Elite 3 Motorcycle Tires
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tread splice failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and serious injury or death, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Rips in the tire tread
cord breakage
and rubber ripping from the inside.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Cracking on Metzler ME880 Marathon GL Front Tires
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracking on the tire sidewalls can lead to tire failure, loss of control, and accidents, potentially causing serious injury or death.
symptoms: Cracking on both sides of the tire
especially after riding 5000+ miles.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Traction Issues with Dunlop 250 Rear Tires
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rear traction issues can cause loss of control, accidents, and serious injury or death, especially at low speeds in wet conditions.
symptoms: Rear tire sliding out from under the motorcycle
front-end wobble
and loss of traction.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front-End Wobble and Handling Issues with Dunlop Tires
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Front-end wobble and handling issues can cause loss of control, accidents, and serious injury or death, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Handlebars shaking
front-end wobble
and loss of traction.
